rial, including the FBI file on Mills.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aSociologistsxBiographyxUnited States. 0aSociologistszUnited StatesvBiography. 4aLetters. 4aLiterary Collections. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Letters.2bisacsh1 aMills, C. Wright, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMills, Kathryn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMills, Pamela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWakefield, Dan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052023209940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092809140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520928091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520928091/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles